How to increase people's access to books? How to encourage people to read more? Since 2013, "nationwide reading" has become China's national policy. What does it mean for Chinese people? On the 27th World Book and Copyright Day, CGTN's Liu Xiaoxian unboxes China's policies to promote reading and figures out how they make reading more accessible for ordinary people. Scriptwriter: Liu Xiaoxian Camera: Yang Shengjie Video editor: Liu Xiaoxian Cover photo designer: Qu Bo Producer: Li Tianfu, Zhu Danni Executive producer: Wen Yaru Supervisor: Zhang Shilei